Fig. 3 | Visitation rates across the three main axes of trait variation. Fitted posterior estimates of the number of visits made by the different floral visitors guilds in relation to PC1, PC2 and PC3. Bees (a, b and c) and the rest of guilds (d, e and f) were plotted separately for visualization purposes. In addition, we trimmed the plotting area that was over the 95th percentile to improve visualisation. PC1 represents the flower number - flower size trade-off, PC2 represents the pollinator dependence trade-off and PC3, the style length trade-off.
